  "text": "These differences can be explained in the context of the changing role of Wnt-signaling during early development. While the early activation of the canonical Wnt/b-catenin pathway is indispensable for the formation of the organizer and the specification of dorsal cell fates, at the onset of gastrulation Wnt (specifically Wnt8) becomes a potent morphogen with ventralizing and posteriorizing effects [CITATION_1] . Due to this later role, pathway activation has to be completely excluded from the dorsal side.",
